3.Count character frequency.

-It wants the frequency of each character.
s = "applesssss"
freq={}
for i in s:
    if i in freq:
        freq[i]+=1
    else:
        freq[i]=1
print(freq)

o/p-->{'a': 1, 'p': 2, 'l': 1, 'e': 1, 's': 5}
TC = O(n)
SC = O(k)
n = length of the string
k = number of unique characters in the string
